r s BC-HKN-STARS-CHANGES-TEX     05-21 0540
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HKN-STARS-CHANGES-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
HITCHCOCK SHAKES UP FIRST LINE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CHAREAN WILLIAMS 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   DENVER _ The road to victory for the Stars is simple: Their
impact players have to have an impact.
</P>
<P>
   Mike Modano, Joe Nieuwendyk and Brett Hull combined for only
three shots in a penalty-marred, 2-0 loss to the Colorado Avalanche
in Game 3 of the Western Conference Finals. The Stars' three-headed
monster has to get more shots for them to have a chance of coming
home today with the best-of-seven series tied.
</P>
<P>
   ``It comes down to us being game-breakers and making a
difference,'' Modano said Saturday. ``...Your key players are
looked upon to have great games. That's going to be the way it has
to be (today) in order for us to give a good chance to win.''
</P>
<P>
   With nothing doing in Game 3, Stars coach Ken Hitchcock decided
to make something happen Saturday. He shook up the team's lines.
</P>
<P>
   Modano and Hull are expected to be joined by Scott Thornton on
the first line. Nieuwendyk will have Mike Keane and Jere Lehtinen
on his second line.
</P>
<P>
   ``What we're looking for right now is to spread the wealth,''
Hitchcock said. ``We're trying to get to where we've got 12
forwards that we know that we can throw them in in any situation
and not be afraid to play them.''
</P>
<P>
   The change can't hurt Nieuwendyk.
</P>
<P>
   Nieuwendyk, who had the game-winning goals in Games 2 and 3 of
the Western Conference Finals against Colorado last year, has no
goals, no assists, three shots, a minus-1 and four penalties in the
series.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's frustrating,'' Nieuwendyk said. ``It's important to get
the puck to the net, but we were having problems getting it
there.''
</P>
<P>
   Nieuwendyk had 11 goals, including six game-winners, and 21
points last year in winning the Conn Smythe Trophy as most valuable
player of the playoffs. In 13 playoff games this year, he has four
goals and three assists. Two of his goals, including the
game-winner, came in a 5-4 victory against San Jose in Game 4 of
the Western Conference semifinals.
</P>
<P>
   ``He knows he's got to get going,'' Hitchcock said. ``He knows
he could be a difference-maker in this series just like he was at
the end of the series against San Jose. This is usually the time
when he steps up, and hopefully he does.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't think it's any secret that when you look at scoring
chances that Modano's line is getting all the scoring chances. From
our standpoint, we've got to get more play from other lines.''
</P>
<P>
   The Stars have only three goals in three games. All three were
scored in Game 2.
</P>
<P>
   Modano, who has eight goals and four assists in the playoffs,
scored twice in Game 2. Hull, who has five goals and nine assists
in the postseason, scored the team's other goal.
</P>
<P>
   Nieuwendyk still is waiting for his first.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's about getting confidence,'' Stars winger Jamie
Langenbrunner said of Nieuwendyk. ``When he gains his confidence,
he can get unstoppable. Maybe he's second-guessing himself. It's
like anything else. If you're a second late, it's not going to
happen. But if you have confidence and just go, go, go, it works
better. We were getting it going, but we haven't been playing with
that same confidence this series.'' nn
</P>
</TEXT>
