NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR MONDAY, MAY 22
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Monday. Days and dates refer to the original article's transmission
by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be adjusted by
NYT clients.)  
(ss) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-WORLD-BRIEFS-NYT (moved Tuesday, May 9)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, May 9
about the overturning of a bribery conviction of the Italian
politician Silvio Berlusconi misstated his coalition's political
stance. It is center-right, not center-left.
</P>
<P>
   BC-OBIT-SAWHILL-NYT (moved Friday, May 19)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service obituary sent on Friday, May 19
about John Sawhill, president and chief executive of the Nature
Conservancy and former president of New York University, misstated
the surname of the dean of the N.Y.U. School of Education, who
reminisced about his management style. She is Ann Marcus, not
Mancuso.
