world are in law enforcement. I'm not talking about the cops who
hunt for pedophiles on AOL or the D.A.s chasing scam artists on
eBay. I'm referring to the scientists and engineers who enforce
Moore's Law, the principle that the number of transistors that can
be packed into a given area of silicon doubles every 18 to 24
months. It's the technical basis for the exponential increases in
processing power and memory capacity that have made high tech as we
know it possible.  &UR; COLUMN BY HENRY NORR &LR;
</P>
