spread across the industry.  &UR; BY HENRY NORR &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; DSL _ &LR;  Flashcom touts its superfast Internet service with a cartoon
turtle, happily sporting aviator's glasses and a rocket strapped to
its back. Meanwhile, EarthLink, Telocity and more than a dozen
other rivals also are peddling digital-subscriber lines, which
offer speedy access to the Net over telephone lines.
 &UR; BY TODD WALLACK &LR;
</P>
