effort against the New York Knicks, as New York defeated Miami for
the third straight year 83-82, Sunday. Although Mourning led the
Heat in scoring, he missed three foul shots in the fourth quarter
when Miami was trying to increase slim leads. The victory sends the
Knicks into the Eastern Conference finals against the Indiana
Pacers. Game 1 is Tuesday night in Indianapolis. (Barton
Silverman/The New York Times)
</P>
