<P>
   (NYT8) NEW YORK -- May 21, 2000 -- PRIESTS-RECRUIT -- At a time
when other dioceses throughout the nation are struggling through a
shortage of priests, Archbishop-designate Edward Egan has
vigorously recruited and ordained a higher proportion of priests
than any other diocese in the Northeast. Underscoring the priority
he sets on building up the priesthood, Egan, officially not New
York's archbishop until his installation on June 19, ordained this
year's graduates of St. Joseph's Seminary at St. Patrick's
Cathedral, Saturday. (Ruth Fremson/The New York Times)
</P>
